content.title: Official Singles Chart on 20/12/2009
content.description: The Official UK Singles Chart reflects the UK’s biggest songs of the week, based on audio and video streams, downloads, CDs and vinyl, compiled by the Official Charts Company. The UK Top 40 is broadcast on BBC Radio 1, the Top 100 is published exclusively on OfficialCharts.com. View the biggest songs of 2024 so far.

children.title: 81f0eec4-4946-41c8-95ad-d96095d628f8
children.body: It May of been #1 in the UK in 2009, but the sales data was taking that year from 13th to 19th December only! From 20th December So Called Christmas Charts here in the UK or #1, but Joe Mcelderry with the Climb was officially Christmas week sales #1 From 27th December Weekly Charts as the sales was taking at Christmas from 20th to 26th December. You See!! Factoid - christmas charts uk broadcasted on media, does never inc: Christmas Day (1st Day Of Christmas) or the week in that matter! Hope it does soon. Maybe one day or one year we all see Christmas Charts after Christmas day broadcast or towards the new year, that be more better!
